 Präsentation der klassischen Bestände sowie die Verfügbarkeit und das Angebot elektronischer Medien inhaltliche Schwerpunkte, zu denen die Vermittlung von Informationskompetenz ganz allgemein sowie die verschiedenen Möglichkeiten der Auskunftserteilung und der Dokumentlieferung gehören. Die Auftritte von Bibliotheken in Web 1.0 und Web 2.0 Plattformen werden unter verschiedensten Aspekten, wie Usability, Informationsgehalt oder den spezifischen Chancen und Risiken bewertet.  aThis book examines modern library use, focusing on the needs of the customer. It covers the storage and presentation of classical holdings as well as digital media. It also addresses the general question of information competency and new options for delivering information. The advent of libraries on Web 1.0 and Web 2.0 platforms with regard to usability, information content, and specific benefits and risks are additionally considered.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aBibliographical servicesxAutomation. 0aDigital mediaxManagement. 0aInformation servicesxAutomationxManagement. 0aLibrary information networks. 0aMachine-readable bibliographic data. 0aOnline bibliographic searching. 0aReference services (Libraries)xAutomation. 4aBenutzung. 4aBestand. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh  aholdings.  alibrary use.1 aGillitzer, Bertold, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKuttner, Sven, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSchwarz, Stephan , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Library Information Science 2000 - 2014z9783110636246oZDB-23-GLI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z978